alert.note: Alert for Interstate 5 Corridor; Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued October 11 at 5:11AM PDT until October 12 at 12:00PM PDT by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON PDT THURSDAY... * WHAT...Areas of northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 50 mph expected through this evening, then winds will become north to northeast 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 50 mph late tonight and Thursday morning. There will be local gusts to 60 mph near the Interstate 5 Corridor through this evening. * WHERE...Interstate 5 Corridor and Western San Gabriel Mountains and Highway 14 Corridor. * WHEN...Until noon PDT Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for drivers of high profile vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
